snippet.textDisplay: I don't think there's been enough discussion of how ridiculous it is that Madonna and Carly Rae Jepsen got snubbed yet again by the Grammys after releasing some of their best work yet. The Academy clearly felt both albums had songs worthy of nominations or even wins, since a remix of I Rise won somebody else a Grammy and one of the nominees for Producer of the Year was nominated for two of the songs on Dedicated, but because Madonna and Carly Rae Jepsen aren't the "it" girl they get no credit. I'm not here to rip Billie Eilish or anyone else (I've already vented about it elsewhere), but I think there's a clear bias in the selection process toward new, young performers, especially those with inroads in the industry. Meanwhile, older/established artists are completely ignored no matter how good their work is.
